---
// What we won't do — engagement-level discipline. Mirrors the /ai page's
// "What We Won't Do With AI" pattern (src/pages/ai.astro:136-182). Self-
// limitation reads as discipline, which reads as competence. This is the
// trust earner that compensates for the absence of shipped case studies
// in pre-launch.
//
// Doctrine: "we" voice, no fixed timeframes, no fabricated outcomes, no
// personalized outreach-promise templates, no em dashes.
const disciplines = [
  {
    title: "We won't promise outcomes we can't scope.",
    body: 'If we cannot draw a clean line around what success looks like, we say so before you commit. Some problems need a conversation before they need a quote, and some are not the ones to fix first. We are not interested in selling you an engagement that ends with you wondering what you actually bought.',
  },
  {
    title: "We won't sell tools we wouldn't use ourselves.",
    body: 'There are vendors out there with good marketing and weak products. If we recommend something, we have used it, run it, or watched it work in a business shaped like yours. When we are not sure, we say that too.',
  },
  {
    title: "We won't run open-ended retainers.",
    body: 'Engagements have a beginning and a handoff. Your team runs what we built when we are done. Ongoing support exists when it makes sense, but it is its own scoped agreement, not a default monthly bill that grows past usefulness.',
  },
  {
    title: "We won't pretend to know what we can't see.",
    body: 'A lot of consulting opens with "we already know what is wrong with your business." From outside, without a conversation, we do not. The serious work starts when we listen. Anyone telling you they can diagnose your business without talking to you is selling something else.',
  },
]
---

<section
  class="bg-[color:var(--ss-color-background)] px-6 py-24 border-t-[3px] border-[color:var(--ss-color-text-primary)]"
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-5xl">
    <div class="mb-16">
      <span
        class="inline-block bg-[color:var(--ss-color-text-primary)] text-[color:var(--ss-color-background)] font-['JetBrains_Mono'] text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] px-2 py-1 mb-4"
        >§ 08</span
      >
      <h2
        class="font-['Archivo'] text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black uppercase tracking-[-0.02em] text-[color:var(--ss-color-text-primary)]"
      >
        What We Won't Do
      </h2>
      <p
        class="mt-6 max-w-2xl font-['Archivo'] text-lg text-pretty text-[color:var(--ss-color-text-secondary)]"
      >
        A few lines we hold because they matter more than any one engagement.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-10 border-t-[3px] pt-10 border-[color:var(--ss-color-text-primary)]">
      {
        disciplines.map((d) => (
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-['Archivo'] text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold uppercase tracking-[-0.01em] text-[color:var(--ss-color-text-primary)]">
              {d.title}
            </h3>
            <p class="mt-3 font-['Archivo'] leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--ss-color-text-secondary)]">
              {d.body}
            </p>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
